# RAG Demo API — Global Architecture Rules

## ENFORCEMENT MODE
These rules are STRICT and MUST be followed.
Violations require refactor before merge.

---

# LAYER ARCHITECTURE

## Order
domain → application → infrastructure → presentation

---

## DOMAIN LAYER

### MUST
- ZERO external dependencies
- ONLY business logic
- ONLY entities, value objects, repository interfaces

### MUST NOT
- import application/infrastructure/presentation
- use NestJS, ORM, HTTP, SDKs

---

## APPLICATION LAYER

### MUST
- implement CQRS (Command / Query / Handler)
- use only Port interfaces
- return DTOs only

### MUST NOT
- import infrastructure
- contain framework logic
- contain business rules

---

## INFRASTRUCTURE LAYER

### MUST
- implement Port interfaces only
- contain all external adapters

### MUST NOT
- contain business logic
- be used directly by application via concrete classes

---

## PRESENTATION LAYER

### MUST
- ONLY dispatch via CommandBus
- ONLY validate input
- ONLY return handler result

### MUST NOT
- contain business logic
- inject services/repositories
- call application/infrastructure directly

---

# DEPENDENCY RULES

### FORBIDDEN CROSS-LAYER IMPORTS
- domain → application ❌
- domain → infrastructure ❌
- application → infrastructure ❌
- presentation → application/services ❌

---

# DI RULES

### REQUIRED
- inject ONLY via string tokens

### FORBIDDEN
- injecting concrete classes anywhere except infrastructure module binding

---

# CQRS RULES

### REQUIRED
- every operation MUST be Command or Query
- every handler MUST expose execute()

### FORBIDDEN
- direct service calls from controllers
- logic inside controllers

---

# REGISTRATION RULE

### REQUIRED
All Commands/Queries MUST be registered in:
RagModule.onModuleInit()

---

### FORBIDDEN
- unregistered handlers
- orphan commands/queries

---

# INFRASTRUCTURE RULES

### REQUIRED
- one module per external system:
  qdrant, neo4j, prisma, redis, s3, ollama

### FORBIDDEN
- shared “god module”
- cross-service coupling

---

# CONFIG RULES

### REQUIRED
- all env/config values must be in ragConfig

### FORBIDDEN
- process.env outside config
- hardcoded URLs, models, credentials

---

# LOGGING RULES

### REQUIRED
- use LoggerPort

### FORBIDDEN
- console.log anywhere

---

# LLM RULES

### REQUIRED
- all model names come from config only

### FORBIDDEN
- hardcoded model names anywhere

---

# PRESENTATION RULES

### REQUIRED
- controllers are pure dispatchers

### FORBIDDEN
- business logic in controllers
- direct service injection

---

# SECURITY RULES

### REQUIRED
- global guards must stay enabled

### FORBIDDEN
- bypassing ThrottlerGuard
- disabling security middleware without explicit reason

---

# GOLDEN RULE

The Application Layer decides NOTHING.
The Domain Layer knows EVERYTHING.
Infrastructure DOES NOTHING but adapt.
Presentation ONLY forwards.